<br>
Honestly, if people are looking for loot on raids and personal gain, a DKP system is ideal for everyone involved.  You too can save up a few months worth of DKP and bid on those super duper items.<br>
<br>
Head on over to your nearest 24/7 raid guild that is into nothing but logging on and killing mobs and apply.  Don't blame the guild because your ideals differ from theirs though.  I tire of seeing how guild leaders are &quot;unfair&quot; and &quot;play favorites&quot; from people who have never had to lead a guild before.  <br>
<br>
Not everyone can be happy, but if your ambition drives you to leave a guild, don't shit on the people doing their best to make your on-line experience better without good cause.  If a person is really greedy, chances are no one will follow that person after a while.<br>
